The paper deals with optimization problems that are neither approximable in polynomial time nor fixed parameter tractable, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on exact exponential-time algorithms and approximation schemes also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The specific problems studied, such as Maximum Independent Set and Vertex Coloring, are often studied in the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of backtracking algorithms and general transformations suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and game theory (cs.GT).
